menu "Mock Driver Configuration"

    config MOCK_FLASH_SIZE_BLOCKS
        int "Mock Flash Size (Blocks)"
        default 1024 if SPIRAM
        default 128
        help
            Number of blocks to simulate in the mock SPI NAND driver.
            Each block consumes memory for the sparse pointer array.
            ESP32-S3 (with more RAM) can support larger mock flash.
            ESP32/C3 should use smaller values (e.g., 128) to avoid running out of RAM.

endmenu
